  • Field Details

    • lhs

      public final Operand<T extends TNumber> lhs
      Must be a 2D Tensor of Tin.

    • rhs

      public final Operand<T extends TNumber> rhs
      Must be a 2D Tensor of Tin.

    • lhsScales

      public final Operand<TFloat32> lhsScales
      The float value(s) used as scale when quantizing original data that lhs represents. Must be a scalar Tensor (lhs supports only per-tensor quantization).

    • lhsZeroPoints

      public final Operand<TInt32> lhsZeroPoints
      The int32 value(s) used as zero_point when quantizing original data that lhs represents. Same shape condition as lhs_scales.

    • rhsScales

      public final Operand<TFloat32> rhsScales
      The float value(s) used as scale when quantizing original data that rhs represents. Must be a scalar Tensor (per-tensor quantization) or 1D Tensor of size (rhs.dim_size(1),) (per-channel quantization).

    • rhsZeroPoints

      public final Operand<TInt32> rhsZeroPoints
      The int32 value(s) used as zero_point when quantizing original data that rhs represents. Same shape condition as rhs_scales.

    • outputScales

      public final Operand<TFloat32> outputScales
      The float value(s) to use as scales when quantizing original data that output represents. Must be a scalar Tensor (per-tensor quantization) or 1D Tensor of size (output.dim_size(1),) (per-channel quantization). If rhs is per-tensor quantized, output must be also per-tensor quantized. This means that if rhs_scales and rhs_zero_points are scalar Tensors, output_scales and output_zero_points must be scalar Tensors as well.

    • outputZeroPoints

      public final Operand<TInt32> outputZeroPoints
      The int32 value(s) used as zero_point when quantizing original data that output represents. Same shape condition as rhs_scales.

    • Tin

      public final DataType Tin
      The type of lhs and rhs input Tensor.

    • Tout

      public final DataType Tout
      The type of output Tensor.

    • lhsQuantizationAxis

      public final long lhsQuantizationAxis
      Indicates the dimension index of the tensor where per-axis quantization is applied for the slices along that dimension. If set to -1 (default), this indicates per-tensor quantization. For dot op lhs, only per-tensor quantization is supported. Thus, this attribute must be set to -1. Other values are rejected.

    • lhsQuantizationMinVal

      public final long lhsQuantizationMinVal
      The min value of the quantized data stored in lhs. For example, if Tin is qint8, this must be set to -127 if narrow range quantized or -128 if not.

    • lhsQuantizationMaxVal

      public final long lhsQuantizationMaxVal
      The max value of the quantized data stored in rhs. For example, if Tin is qint8, this must be set to 127.

    • rhsQuantizationAxis

      public final long rhsQuantizationAxis
      Indicates the dimension index of the tensor where per-axis quantization is applied for the slices along that dimension. If set to -1 (default), this indicates per-tensor quantization. For dot op rhs, only per-tensor quantization or per-channel quantization along dimension 1 is supported. Thus, this attribute must be set to -1 or 1. Other values are rejected.

    • rhsQuantizationMinVal

      public final long rhsQuantizationMinVal
      The min value of the quantized data stored in rhs. For example, if Trhs is qint8, this must be set to -127 if narrow range quantized or -128 if not.

    • rhsQuantizationMaxVal

      public final long rhsQuantizationMaxVal
      The max value of the quantized data stored in rhs. For example, if Trhs is qint8, this must be set to 127.

    • outputQuantizationAxis

      public final long outputQuantizationAxis
      Indicates the dimension index of the tensor where per-axis quantization is applied for the slices along that dimension. If set to -1 (default), this indicates per-tensor quantization. For dot op output, only per-tensor quantization or per-channel quantization along dimension 1 is supported. Thus, this attribute must be set to -1 or 1. Other values are rejected.

    • outputQuantizationMinVal

      public final long outputQuantizationMinVal
      The min value of the quantized data stored in output. For example, if Tout is qint8, this must be set to -127 if narrow range quantized or -128 if not.

    • outputQuantizationMaxVal

      public final long outputQuantizationMaxVal
      The max value of the quantized data stored in output. For example, if Tout is qint8, this must be set to 127.
